// Two parallel loops sharing a post-block. Neither loop's header dominates
// the post-block (block 3), so the NMG dom check (Algorithm 2 line 8) keeps
// block 3 in succ_nodes for both loops and out of either loop's loop_nodes.
// The structurer emits both Reduced loops as siblings inside an if/else,
// with Block(3) as the trailing sibling - no gotos, no synthetic sinks.
//
// 0 → 1, 4
// 1 → 2, 3     (loop A head; back-edge from 2)
// 2 → 1
// 4 → 5, 3     (loop B head; back-edge from 5)
// 5 → 4
// 3 → return

cond,0,1,4
cond,1,2,3
code,2,1
cond,4,5,3
code,5,4
code,3
